column49: I am very disappointed about the cost of the books.   I spend out of my own pocket to make sure my students have a monthly book from me.   I have spent hundreds and hundred of dollars.  Now your book of the week has gone up to 2.00 and you no longer have  10 books for $10.  Book prices have doubled.  I use to rave over how wonderful scholastic is and even push my parents to buy books from your monthly catalogs.  Even 2 years ago when it took over a month to get orders I still stood by you and knew I would eventually get my books. Then we leave for the summer and come back and  it is all different and costly. We live in an socio economically depressed area and parents are not going to be able to afford to shop at these prices either.

column49: Book clubs needs to allow teachers the flexibility to choose our own due dates. I understand after talking to a representative that you guys deciding the due date is "to make it easier on teachers", but it completely messes up the way I normally use book clubs. Can I adjust? Sure, but it's really disappointing to have ZERO control over this feature. Teachers need to be able to run the things in their classrooms the way they want and need to. We don't need another entity telling us how to do our job and that's how I feel you are treating us, like we can't do it ourselves. No better than the government. I do like going away from class codes, but the due date needs to have the flexibility of the teacher's discretion.
